==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[μελαγχολικός]]''' (''melancholikos'') "atrabilious, impulsive, of atrabilious or melancholic temperament" from '''[[μελαγχολία]]''' (''melancholia'') "[[melancholy]]".

===Adjective===
'''melancholic'''

# [[fill]]ed with or [[affect]]ed by [[melancholy]]

